-- West Ham Beats Cardiff 3-0 to Get to Championship Promotion Game
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-05-07T20:51:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/west-ham-beats-cardiff-3-0-to-get-to-championship-promotion-game.html
West Ham beat Cardiff 3-0 at home in
the second leg of their Championship playoff match, putting the
 London  team into the final to decide what promotion to English
soccer’s Premier League.  West Ham won 2-0 at Cardiff and so takes the two-game
competition 5-0. The Hammers will play Birmingham or Blackpool
May 19 at Wembley Stadium in London. Blackpool has a 1-0 lead
going into the second game at Birmingham tomorrow.  West Ham captain  Kevin Nolan  scored in the 15th minute, and
Ricardo Vaz Te added one just before halftime. Substitute Nicky
Maynard finished the scoring in the 90th minute.  Reading and Southampton have already been promoted to
England’s top league. West Ham finished third in the
Championship, so entered the playoffs against sixth-place
Cardiff.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  